    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/cou1-cpb-decision-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team has reviewed all 13 ASME V&V 40 factors for COU1 and concludes that the CFD model is sufficiently credible for the intended use. Seven factors were formally assessed; six were appropriately scoped out at MRL 2. All assessed factors are judged to meet their required credibility levels. The discretization error factor demonstrated consistent monotonic mesh convergence across three refinement levels, and the team's accumulated experience with this pump class, combined with the relative nature of the acceptance criterion (RH < 1), supports the conclusion that residual discretization uncertainty does not affect the worst-case operating condition identification. The validation activities were conducted on the identical pump geometry under representative CPB conditions, and output comparison agreement (mean error 8.3%) is within acceptable bounds for comparative hemolysis assessment. No unresolved credibility gaps were identified that would preclude acceptance of the model for this COU. Decision: Accepted.",
